      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KUEBIKO (2) has missed the placings at his last two but was third at this track three back and returns to Mt Gambier where he tends to run well. Look for sharp improvement here. LITTLE BUTTON (1) comes off an average effort last start when eighth at Shepparton over 390m behind Dundee Spike (23.10) in a T3 Grade 7. One of the better hopes. PRESSURE POINT (4) started big odds but ran a huge race last time when finishing 2nd over 342m at Angle Park (20.26)in TG1-4W. Was a winner this track in lesser company the start prior. Has a good record here at this journey. Expected to feature. PUDDIN' CAKE (8) is a last-start placegetter worth considering.",
